Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry and season with half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @salt and @pepper.

> Use all the garlic powder and all the paprika if cooking for 4 servings.

Drizzle @cooking oil{} in a hot large pan. Cook chicken until cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

While chicken cooks, wash and dry produce. Massage @microwavable grain blend{1} in package to separate grains. Partially open package; microwave until warmed through, ~{1 1/2-2%minutes}.

Quarter @tomato{1} lengthwise, then cut crosswise into quarter-moons. Thinly slice @mini cucumber{1} and @radishes{3}.

== Chimichurri Mayo ==

In a #small bowl{}, mix @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} with half the @chimichurri{2%ounce}.

== Vinaigrette and Assembly ==

In a #large bowl{}, whisk @red wine vinegar{5%tsp} with remaining chimichurri and a large drizzle of @olive oil{}.

Add tomato, cucumber, radishes, @edamame{4%ounce}, @arugula{2%ounce}, and grain blend to bowl with vinaigrette. Toss to combine; season with @salt and @pepper.

Top salad with chicken and drizzle with chimichurri mayo. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.